Handling a calendar widget in Selenium WebDriver involves interacting with
> date pickers or calendar popups <
that are commonly used in web applications to allow users to select dates.

Since calendars can vary greatly in their HTML structure and behavior, the approach can differ based on the specific implementation.

Common Steps to Handle a Calendar:

Locate and Click the Calendar Widget:
Click on the calendar input field or button to open the calendar widget.

Identify the Date Elements:
Use locators to identify the days, months, or years in the calendar.

Navigate Through the Calendar (Optional):
Some calendars require navigating through months or years if the desired date is not in the current view.

Select the Desired Date:
Click on the desired date to select it.

Handling Dynamic Calendars:

  // Open the calendar widget
            WebElement dateInput = driver.findElement(By.id("calendarInput"));
            dateInput.click();

            // Loop to navigate through months
            while (true) {
                // Find the displayed month and year
                WebElement displayedMonthYear = driver.findElement(By.className("ui-datepicker-title"));

                // Check if the displayed month/year matches the desired date
                if (displayedMonthYear.getText().equals("August 2024")) {
                    break;
                }

                // If not, click the next button to navigate
                WebElement nextButton = driver.findElement(By.xpath("//a[@title='Next']"));
                nextButton.click();
            }

            // Select the desired day
            WebElement date = driver.findElement(By.xpath("//td[@data-day='15']"));
            date.click();
        } finally {
            // Close the browser
            driver.quit();
        }

Selecting Date Using JavaScript Executor (Alternative Approach):

            // Use JavaScript to set the date directly
            JavascriptExecutor js = (JavascriptExecutor) driver;
            js.executeScript("document.getElementById('calendarInput').value = '2024-08-15';");